<item>
            <title>[SPARK-2140] yarn stable client doesn&apos;t properly handle MEMORY_OVERHEAD for AM</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2140</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The yarn stable client doesn&apos;t properly remove the MEMORY_OVERHEAD amount from the java heap size, the code to handle that is commented out (see function calculateAMMemory).  We should fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12721125">SPARK-2140</key>
            <summary>yarn stable client doesn&apos;t properly handle MEMORY_OVERHEAD for AM</summary>
